## ✅ Expected Output

| emp_id | name  | dept    | emp_salary | city      |
| ------ | ----- | ------- | ---------: | --------- |
| 101    | John  | IT      |      60000 | Mumbai    |
| 102    | David | HR      |      45000 | Delhi     |
| 103    | Alice | IT      |      70000 | Pune      |
| 104    | Bob   | Finance |      55000 | Hyderabad |
| 105    | Sam   | HR      |      48000 | Chennai   |

---

# ✅ Solution 1 – Rename One Column

```python
df = df.withColumnRenamed("department", "dept")

df.show()
```

---

# ✅ Solution 2 – Rename Another Column

```python
df = df.withColumnRenamed("salary", "emp_salary")

df.show()
```

---

# ✅ Solution 3 – Rename Multiple Columns (Recommended)

```python
df = (
    df.withColumnRenamed("department", "dept")
      .withColumnRenamed("salary", "emp_salary")
)

df.show()
```

---

# ⭐ Alternative Solution

If you want to rename **all** columns at once:

```python
df = df.toDF(
    "emp_id",
    "name",
    "dept",
    "emp_salary",
    "city"
)
```

This is useful when renaming many or all columns.

